579
00:59:28,057 --> 00:59:32,179
[SPEAKER_04]: So, you know, that money's going away, but the free cash target, it seems ad hoc.

580
00:59:32,199 --> 00:59:37,362
[SPEAKER_04]: And I heard you say, you know, we're not sure 2025, fiscal 25 free cash is going to be as strong, et cetera.

581
00:59:38,192 --> 00:59:59,524
[SPEAKER_04]: Do you think it's possible to set like a percentage target for how much of free cash we should be allocating towards capital expenditures every year, rather than just kind of saying, well we think free cash isn't going to be great so we'll use 750,000 or is that just not something that you guys do have seen in other communities.

582
01:00:04,051 --> 01:00:07,453
[SPEAKER_03]: It is something that some communities do.

583
01:00:08,714 --> 01:00:22,082
[SPEAKER_03]: What I have seen in terms of financial policies around free cash use is something along the lines of, we are going to appropriate no less than 25% of free cash into a capital stabilization fund.

584
01:00:22,802 --> 01:00:28,664
[SPEAKER_03]: We are going to appropriate no less than 25% of free cash into a general stabilization fund.

585
01:00:29,144 --> 01:00:37,868
[SPEAKER_03]: And then the rest is left to be available for various uses that the city should decide upon.

586
01:00:38,548 --> 01:00:46,891
[SPEAKER_03]: So that is actually a really appropriate approach.

587
01:00:47,151 --> 01:00:49,232
[SPEAKER_03]: Setting a free cash dollar target

588
01:00:52,440 --> 01:01:02,127
[SPEAKER_03]: is one way to do it, but using a capital stabilization fund and committing to a percentage of free cash allows you to be flexible.

589
01:01:02,187 --> 01:01:10,514
[SPEAKER_03]: So you don't know if your free cash is gonna come in up here or down here, but no matter where it comes in, you're committing a certain percentage of that right to your capital stabilization fund.

590
01:01:10,594 --> 01:01:16,118
[SPEAKER_03]: And that capital stabilization fund then becomes the source of pay-go capital.

591
01:01:16,778 --> 01:01:37,811
[SPEAKER_03]: So rather than using free cash directly, you have it sort of passed through the capital stabilization fund in a way that gives you consistent funding for capital, commits the city or town by policy to funding that, and it just kind of creates a more consistent resource for cash capital.

592
01:01:38,051 --> 01:01:41,894
[SPEAKER_03]: So it's something that I would absolutely recommend the city consider.

593
01:01:43,641 --> 01:01:44,722
[SPEAKER_04]: Yeah, that's really helpful.

594
01:01:44,742 --> 01:01:54,427
