662
01:08:44,427 --> 01:08:53,613
[SPEAKER_03]: I will just say that, you know, certainly establishing a capital stabilization fund is a, you know, you're committing to using that money for capital.

663
01:08:53,713 --> 01:08:55,995
[SPEAKER_03]: So it's certainly, in a way,

664
01:08:57,706 --> 01:09:02,627
[SPEAKER_03]: It's different from using just straight free cash, because free cash, when it comes up, there's always a conversation.

665
01:09:02,647 --> 01:09:11,129
[SPEAKER_03]: There's always a pull between multiple needs, whereas a capital stabilization fund is designated for capital and restricted to capital.

666
01:09:11,949 --> 01:09:22,351
[SPEAKER_03]: And so it does kind of create a nice, dedicated funding source rather than having a fight each time if there are multiple needs that are pulling at your free cash.

