763
01:19:07,882 --> 01:19:09,823
[SPEAKER_03]: So there's a little bit.

764
01:19:09,903 --> 01:19:10,684
[SPEAKER_04]: I just want to push back.

765
01:19:10,704 --> 01:19:13,385
[SPEAKER_04]: I mean, I think that's an ideological frame.

766
01:19:14,065 --> 01:19:14,526
[SPEAKER_04]: It's not.

767
01:19:15,266 --> 01:19:15,826
[SPEAKER_04]: It's a choice.

768
01:19:15,886 --> 01:19:16,427
[SPEAKER_04]: We have a choice.

769
01:19:16,467 --> 01:19:17,527
[SPEAKER_04]: We have a set of needs.

770
01:19:18,168 --> 01:19:21,409
[SPEAKER_04]: We can choose to raise the revenue to meet those needs, or we can choose not to.

771
01:19:21,870 --> 01:19:30,795
[SPEAKER_04]: But saying we have to accept poor conditioned roads because it's a burden on the taxpayers otherwise, I just think that's an ideological frame, and I don't think it should be part of the conversation here.

772
01:19:30,815 --> 01:19:32,275
[SPEAKER_02]: Fair.

773
01:19:34,116 --> 01:19:34,877
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you, Vice Chair Behrs.

774
01:19:34,897 --> 01:19:36,038
