785
01:20:49,377 --> 01:20:54,823
[SPEAKER_03]: So the first line is the total of free cash funded projects each year.

786
01:20:55,364 --> 01:21:00,829
[SPEAKER_03]: And then the next line is comparing that number to the target and showing the surplus or deficit.

787
01:21:02,531 --> 01:21:05,194
[SPEAKER_03]: So you can see in 23, there's a slight surplus.

788
01:21:05,254 --> 01:21:06,996
[SPEAKER_03]: In 24, there's a slight deficit.

789
01:21:09,290 --> 01:21:15,778
[SPEAKER_03]: $15,000 here or there in the grand scheme of things is not something that I would really push to resolve.

790
01:21:15,798 --> 01:21:23,386
[SPEAKER_03]: We're never going to get perfect balance, but you can see that over the years, collectively, there is a surplus.

791
01:21:24,267 --> 01:21:35,451
[SPEAKER_03]: And so it's interesting because this plan that we've developed shows a surplus from free cash, a pretty significant surplus in what I call the out years, especially 27 and 28.

792
01:21:35,491 --> 01:21:36,292
[SPEAKER_03]: Why did we leave it like that?

793
01:21:41,677 --> 01:21:44,340
[SPEAKER_03]: Sometimes it can be difficult to plan that far out.

794
01:21:45,321 --> 01:21:54,550
[SPEAKER_03]: And so department heads use their best judgment with the full knowledge that on an annual basis, this plan needs to be re-examined and updated.

795
01:21:54,930 --> 01:22:03,819
[SPEAKER_03]: And I would fully expect that those dollars would be attributed to projects that we don't know about right now, but will come up over the next couple of years.

796
01:22:06,505 --> 01:22:16,949
[SPEAKER_03]: All right, so moving down to the next block there, the ARPA block, we've got the first line, which shows how much money the projects are costing us.

797
01:22:17,630 --> 01:22:19,170
[SPEAKER_03]: And then we have the surplus deficit.

798
01:22:19,210 --> 01:22:24,892
[SPEAKER_03]: So you can see, we brought it right up to the line there, funded all of the projects, used all of the money.

799
01:22:24,913 --> 01:22:30,755
[SPEAKER_03]: We have a slight deficit totaling a little over 12,000, but that's not really material at this point.

800
01:22:32,695 --> 01:22:35,016
[SPEAKER_03]: The third block covers debt service.

801
01:22:35,496 --> 01:22:42,119
[SPEAKER_03]: So the annual general fund debt service projected for the projects that we've identified to be funded with general fund debt.

802
01:22:42,780 --> 01:22:47,002
[SPEAKER_03]: And I should say using conservative assumptions around interest rates.

803
01:22:48,785 --> 01:22:49,667
[SPEAKER_03]: is as follows.

804
01:22:49,727 --> 01:23:02,584
[SPEAKER_03]: So you can see that in 2024 that number is 538,933 for all projects except for those two major building projects that I told you about, FHIR headquarters and MHS.

805
