841
01:26:28,661 --> 01:26:39,643
[SPEAKER_03]: So it's just something to keep in mind and obviously spend a lot of time thinking and planning for as you get closer and closer to those projects kind of closer to reality in terms of construction.

842
01:26:39,663 --> 01:26:47,005
[SPEAKER_03]: And then at the bottom, I have the proposed enterprise fund spending plan.

843
01:26:47,025 --> 01:26:47,945
[SPEAKER_03]: And again, the

844
01:26:50,939 --> 01:26:56,080
[SPEAKER_03]: I've broken it into PAYGO, which is the cash funded, typically from retained earnings, and then the debt service.

845
01:26:56,120 --> 01:27:00,081
[SPEAKER_03]: So this is just for new debt associated with the Enterprise Fund.

846
01:27:00,481 --> 01:27:05,443
[SPEAKER_03]: You can see that we've kind of kept it around $800 to $1.3 million.

847
01:27:07,043 --> 01:27:15,405
[SPEAKER_03]: And we would anticipate that these would all be funded with Enterprise Fund dollars raised through the rates.

848
01:27:22,121 --> 01:27:27,266
[SPEAKER_03]: All right, so just some final thoughts before I wrap up and I'm happy to take additional questions.

849
01:27:27,446 --> 01:27:30,389
