850
01:27:30,589 --> 01:27:34,673
[SPEAKER_03]: It does require ongoing review and it requires ongoing management.

851
01:27:34,693 --> 01:27:39,178
[SPEAKER_03]: If you do a plan, and you know, this applies to any type of plan.

852
01:27:39,458 --> 01:27:47,485
[SPEAKER_03]: do a plan and then let it live on the shelf or live in a folder and you never use it, manage it, then you've kind of missed an opportunity.

853
01:27:47,565 --> 01:27:55,412
[SPEAKER_03]: So certainly I would encourage the city's administration to actively manage the capital improvement plan.

854
01:27:56,842 --> 01:27:58,543
[SPEAKER_03]: Capital planning is an annual process.

855
01:27:58,623 --> 01:28:02,346
[SPEAKER_03]: It has to be done every year to maintain a robust and accurate plan.

856
01:28:03,567 --> 01:28:10,752
[SPEAKER_03]: We can expect, we should expect that sometimes the scope of a project changes or priorities can change or funding sources can change.

857
01:28:11,152 --> 01:28:16,956
[SPEAKER_03]: We may have in the plan attributed a certain project to CPA funding, but you know what?

858
01:28:17,216 --> 01:28:18,417
[SPEAKER_03]: They get to make their own decisions.

859
01:28:18,477 --> 01:28:20,678
[SPEAKER_03]: The CPC is an independent body.

860
01:28:20,718 --> 01:28:21,899
[SPEAKER_03]: They may say, no, thank you.

861
01:28:22,179 --> 01:28:26,042
[SPEAKER_03]: And then we need to find a different source of funding for the project if we still want to fund it.

862
01:28:26,142 --> 01:28:32,990
[SPEAKER_03]: So there are a lot of assumptions built in around grants, and if things don't work out the way we want them to, we need to find other funding sources.

863
01:28:36,014 --> 01:28:41,640
[SPEAKER_03]: other city efforts really do have an impact on the CIP and can change it fairly significantly.

864
01:28:42,922 --> 01:28:46,946
[SPEAKER_03]: The future of the high school is one prime example.

865
01:28:46,986 --> 01:28:49,829
[SPEAKER_03]: It's such a significant and important project.

866
01:28:50,430 --> 01:28:53,213
[SPEAKER_03]: And should it move forward?

867
01:28:53,313 --> 01:28:56,697
[SPEAKER_03]: Depending on how that looks, it's going to impact the capital plan, absolutely.

868
01:28:58,457 --> 01:29:03,619
[SPEAKER_03]: Just a note on the pandemic and sort of what's been going on over the last several years.

869
01:29:04,700 --> 01:29:06,640
[SPEAKER_03]: As I think I said, it's kind of been whiplash.

870
01:29:07,261 --> 01:29:25,228
[SPEAKER_03]: At first there were some real dire consequences and projected and some negative things happened as regard local government finances, but then we had ESSER funds and we had ARPA funds and we have federal legislation that's opening the door to all sorts of infrastructure funding.

871
01:29:25,908 --> 01:29:30,573
[SPEAKER_03]: So there are some strange things going on in local government finance right now.

872
01:29:30,693 --> 01:29:32,795
[SPEAKER_03]: And it has a particular impact on capital planning.

873
01:29:32,835 --> 01:29:35,197
[SPEAKER_03]: So it's just something to really be mindful of.

874
01:29:35,898 --> 01:29:46,388
[SPEAKER_03]: I know the finance team is mindful of that in the city as they kind of work through how are we going to maximize the opportunities to really get investment for the residents of Medford.

875
01:29:49,690 --> 01:29:55,353
[SPEAKER_03]: you know, there are local and state ARPA funds, as well as those federal infrastructure dollars.

876
01:29:55,673 --> 01:30:00,875
[SPEAKER_03]: And, you know, having a robust plan really sets you up for taking advantage of them.

877
01:30:00,895 --> 01:30:03,757
[SPEAKER_03]: And I think you have the human resources to do so.

878
01:30:03,777 --> 01:30:08,799
[SPEAKER_03]: And I just want to kind of end by saying I really applaud the department heads

879
01:30:09,780 --> 01:30:17,506
[SPEAKER_03]: As they've kind of walked this process with me, I know it's challenging at times to pull yourself away from the day-to-day and think bigger picture.

880
01:30:17,806 --> 01:30:28,075
[SPEAKER_03]: There was a lot of information that we requested from them, a lot of back and forth, a lot of questions, and I just want to thank them for all of the work that they did to get to this point.

881
01:30:32,069 --> 01:30:32,669
[SPEAKER_03]: And that's it.

882
01:30:33,109 --> 01:30:34,410
[SPEAKER_03]: I'm happy to take questions.

883
01:30:35,010 --> 01:30:37,831
[SPEAKER_03]: As I had said, I will share the PowerPoint.

884
01:30:38,332 --> 01:30:43,794
[SPEAKER_03]: I will share the list of the full project so that you can see it.

885
01:30:45,555 --> 01:30:49,236
[SPEAKER_03]: And of course, I'm happy to answer questions now.

886
01:30:49,396 --> 01:30:52,657
[SPEAKER_03]: And if there are follow-up questions at a later date, I will do so as well.

887
01:30:52,697 --> 01:30:53,778
[SPEAKER_03]: I'm just going to turn my light on.

888
01:30:56,228 --> 01:30:56,768
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you, sir.

889
