[SPEAKER_04]: better getting better acquainted with free cash and how we can manage it and how we can work on it.

936
01:35:01,936 --> 01:35:06,739
[SPEAKER_04]: Um so I think those those are two great things, but I really just want to echo Councillor Collins point.

937
01:35:07,059 --> 01:35:10,101
[SPEAKER_04]: Um, you know, we have we have a community.

938
01:35:10,141 --> 01:35:22,990
[SPEAKER_04]: We have a city that city has capital assets that everybody uses the state of a good repair for those assets is a choice that we set democratically as a community and a choice that we've been for a very, very long time for decades in the city.

939
01:35:24,074 --> 01:35:28,695
[SPEAKER_04]: some of it due to what the state says we can and can't do, have not been fulfilling.

940
01:35:28,935 --> 01:35:33,317
[SPEAKER_04]: So we need to move forward and be honest with the community about the community community.

941
01:35:33,337 --> 01:35:41,879
[SPEAKER_04]: I think everyone in the community agrees that they want good roads and safe parks and all of our city's capital assets to be in good repair and well maintained.

942
01:35:42,380 --> 01:35:47,821
[SPEAKER_04]: The question is, is the city finally going to give the residents the choice to raise the money to make that happen?

943
01:35:47,981 --> 01:35:50,122
[SPEAKER_04]: And I think that is the ultimate question here.

944
01:35:50,222 --> 01:35:53,703
[SPEAKER_04]: So thank you for the presentation and I look forward to continuing the work.

945
